// XTermTerminal
// Native xterm.js terminal connected to the Bun PTY backend over WebSocket.
// Renders a full-size terminal with FitAddon for responsive sizing.
// All initialization is deferred until the wrapper element has non-zero
// dimensions (via ResizeObserver). The terminal is re-created when wsUrl or
// sessionId change.

WebSocket URL format: /terminal/:sessionId (relative to window.location.origin).
Messages from server: JSON {type: "output"|"exit"|"error", data/message}.
Messages to server: JSON {type: "input"|"resize", data/cols/rows/isInitial}.
Right-click copies selected text to clipboard.
Scroll events are stopped from propagating to parent containers.

FUNCTION XTermTerminal(wsUrl, sessionId, className) -> JSX             EXPORT
  On mount (or when wsUrl/sessionId change):
  1. Observes wrapper element with ResizeObserver.
     - When wrapper first gets non-zero dimensions: calls initializeTerminal.
     - On subsequent resize events: calls safeFit.
  2. Observes wrapper with IntersectionObserver (threshold 1.0).
     - When fully visible after init: calls safeFit.
  3. Registers window resize handler -> safeFit.
  4. Registers contextmenu handler -> copies xterm selection to clipboard.
  5. Registers wheel handler -> stops propagation.
  On unmount: disconnects all observers, closes WebSocket, disposes xterm,
  clears all refs.

---

FUNCTION sendResize(cols, rows, isInitial) -> void
  Sends {type:"resize", cols, rows, isInitial} JSON over the WebSocket if open.

---

FUNCTION safeFit() -> void
  Skips if disposed or container has zero dimensions.
  Debounces via cancelAnimationFrame + double-RAF. On second RAF, calls
  fitAddon.fit() then sendResize with updated cols/rows.

---

FUNCTION initializeTerminal() -> void
  Guards against double-initialization and disposed state.
  Creates xterm Terminal (80x24, dark theme, 10000 line scrollback).
  Loads FitAddon, opens terminal in DOM, performs initial fit.
  Creates WebSocket connection to /terminal/:sessionId.
  On open: sends initial resize.
  On message: parses JSON; writes output/exit/error to terminal; falls back
  to raw write if not JSON.
  On close: writes "Connection closed" in red.
  Forwards terminal key input as {type:"input"} messages.
  Forwards terminal resize events as {type:"resize"} messages.
